<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILLS COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dichotomy: As a former student politician, I find some satisfaction that the 
students of Mills were successful in directing their institution to remain all 
female (Part A, May 19). 
</P>
<P>
As a human, however, I am appalled at the utter hypocrisy of their feminism. 
OK, girls, you've got it. Now just leave my men's club alone! 
</P>
<P>
CARL G. HOKANSON 
</P>
<P>
Encino 
</P>
</TEXT>
