<P>
Lunev Is Staying: Soviet dancer Aleksandr Lunev, who stunned Boston audiences 
with his soaring leaps in the glasnost "Swan Lake" this month, is joining the 
Boston Ballet for the 1990-91 season. Lunev, disenchanted with the 
opportunities he was receiving from his home Kirov company in Leningrad, landed 
in Boston in early April with just the clothes on his back. He quickly was 
signed to dance major roles in the historic Soviet-American "Swan Lake" 
collaborative production, which ended Sunday. GREG BRAXTON 
