<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorcyclist was killed when he lost control of the cycle while rounding a 
curve in the 9600 block of Black Mountain Road in the Miramar area, authorities 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Almer B. Hedges, 30, of Clairemont died at the scene shortly after 10 p.m. 
Saturday, a spokesman for the coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
He was not wearing a helmet. 
</P>
<P>
Cara Hawkins, 20, a passenger on the motorcycle, was taken to Scripps Memorial 
Hospital in La Jolla with minor injuries. She was in good condition Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Hawkins told investigators that she and Hedges had been drinking at a party for 
an hour and a half before the accident, said Sgt. Fred England, a police 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Hedges was eastbound on Black Mountain Road near Kearny Villa Road when he lost 
control of the cycle, struck a curb on the north side of the road and was 
hurled into a chain-link fence and tree, investigators said. 
</P>
