SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SA DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorcycle passenger was fatally injured in a Hillcrest collision Sunday and 
died later at Mercy Hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Peggy Piseno, 45, was thrown from the motorcycle when a car "violated the 
motorcycle's right of way" near the corner of Washington Street and 9th Avenue 
at 4:53 p.m., San Diego Police spokesman Sgt. Fred England said. 
</P>
<P>
England said the car was attempting to turn south, from Washington onto 9th, 
when it struck the motorcycle, which was heading east on Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the motorcycle, whose name was not released, sustained minor 
injuries. The driver of the car, whose name was not released, was not injured, 
England said. 
