<P>
Capital Cities Sued: A copyright infringement suit was filed in U.S. District 
Court on Tuesday by Motion Picture Holdings Inc., a film distributor, against 
Capital Cities/ABC Inc. The suit, filed in Los Angeles, claims that Capital 
infringed on the plaintiff's copyrights by broadcasting unauthorized 
duplications of seven movies on KABC-TV in Los Angeles and KGO-TV in San 
Francisco. The suit seeks orders barring the airing of more alleged 
unauthorized reproductions and unstated damages from Capital Cities and Acama 
Films, which does business as Movie Greats Network of Sherman Oaks. (Filed May 
15, 1990. Case No. 90-2451) 
