<P>
Pianist Sonya Kumiki Lee, 15, of Laguna Hills, has won the $500 Long Beach 
Philharmonic Juniors third place award in the 1990 Bronsilaw Kaper Award for 
Young Artists competition, sponsored by the Los Angeles Philharmonic. A 
ninth-grader at St. Margaret's School in San Juan Capistrano, Lee won for 
playing Tchaikovsky's First Piano Concerto. 
