<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
OFFICER KILLS MAN IN CLOWN SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young Latino man reportedly wearing a clown suit was shot and killed by a San 
Diego police officer after the man assaulted two highway patrolmen with a 
bricklayer's tool and threatened commuters on a busy freeway this morning, 
police said. The unidentified victim, believed to be in his late 20s, was 
killed when San Diego Police Officer Thomas K. O'Connell fired about eight 
shots from his semiautomatic weapon. 
</P>
<P>
The man was pronounced dead at the scene, on the southbound lanes of Interstate 
5 near La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Robinson, a San Diego police spokesman, said the incident began shortly 
before 8 a.m. when officers spotted the man walking on the freeway's shoulder. 
The victim charged at two California Highway Patrol officers who responded to 
the call, swinging a trowel and striking both of them during a struggle in the 
middle of the freeway, Robinson said. The extent of their injuries was unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
