<P>
Actress Angela Lansbury has received her first college degree, an honorary 
doctorate of humane letters from Boston University. 
</P>
<P>
"I never went to college," the star of television's "Murder, She Wrote" said 
after receiving her degree Sunday. "I left school at 12 for acting classes and 
I've been in the theater ever since.". . . Vanna White, of Wheel of Fortune 
fame, will turn her T-A-L-E-N-T-S to the Home Shopping Network on Tuesday 
morning. Vanna will be hawking bedding and household accessories . . . and you 
guessed it, they're calling it a "White Sale." 
</P>
