<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PROFESSOR HEAD OF THE CLASS AT BELMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Team Clover Stable's The Professor saved ground while racing close to the 
leaders, then came off the rail in mid-stretch under the urging of Chris Antley 
to beat D'Parrot by a nose in the $119,000 Mike Lee Handicap on Sunday at 
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
D'Parrot, ridden by Jerry Bailey, prevailed by 3 1/2 lengths over Power Bolt in 
the race for horses aged 3 and up. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the second in six starts this year for The Professor, who 
covered 1 mile on a fast track in 1:36 4/5 to earn $71,400. 
</P>
</TEXT>
